From Stephen Thomas Subject Re How can I use the mouse in NON Windows applications under MS WINDOWS In article ucsu Colorado EDU, gonzaled ucsu Colorado EDU LGV MC writes Kenneth Kasajian writes Oliver Kretzschmar writes Hey, could somebody tell me, how it is possible to work with the mouse in a NON Windows application, which runs in an window We use MS WINDOWS and have CLIPPER applications Exists there any routines or something else Please mail me your informations Thanks for your efforts, Oliver NAME O Kretzschmar Inst IKE University Stuttgart PHONE Pfaffenwaldring FAX Stuttgart EMAIL Very simple You have to have the MOUSE COM or MOUSE SYS loaded in DOS before you run Windows Note that you don't need to have these files loaded to use the mouse in Windows One addition to this I don't know if it applies to everybody For my Microsoft dpi mouse to work with windowed DOS apps, I had to use the driver that came with Windows Version didn't allow me to do it for some reason I could never find the Microsoft mouse driver on my Windows installation disks, but DOS also has version of MOUSE COM Stephen Thomas AT T Tridom email , attmail tridom sat